<subSubSection id="2DF0ACA1FFE6FFD9FF71FE40FDE4FD62" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="description">
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFE6FFD9FF71FE40FCC7FE03" blockId="14.[151,1437,366,717]" box="[151,826,402,429]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
(
<figureCitation id="FDD1E3AFFFE6FFD9FF79FE40FF14FE02" box="[159,233,402,428]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="59.[151,250,1976,2000]" captionTargetBox="[224,1364,194,1945]" captionTargetId="figure-19@59.[214,1373,181,1952]" captionTargetPageId="59" captionText="FIGURE 6. Neotropical Eudocima, Tetrisia, and Graphigona adults (dorsal aspect)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6605510" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6605510/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Figs 6</figureCitation>
: C–D, 18: B, 23: E, 30: C, 71: C, 72: C, 91: C–D, H)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFE6FFD9FF71FE65FDE4FD62" blockId="14.[151,1437,366,717]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
In this large (
<quantity id="A21252CFFFE6FFD9FECBFE64FE54FE7F" box="[301,425,438,465]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="5.6" metricValueMin="4.4" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" unit="mm" value="50.0" valueMax="56.0" valueMin="44.0">44–56 mm</quantity>
) species the dorsal hindwing medial patch does not reach the wing margin. It is separated from 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFE6FFD9FF33FE09FEBDFE5A" baseAuthorityName="Cramer" baseAuthorityYear="1777" box="[213,320,475,500]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="procus">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFE6FFD9FF33FE09FEBDFE5A" box="[213,320,475,500]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">E. procus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as described above. The dorsal forewing of 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFE6FFD9FCD5FE09FC27FE5A" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1858" box="[819,986,474,500]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serpentifera">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFE6FFD9FCD5FE09FC27FE5A" box="[819,986,474,500]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">E. serpentifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
females has a light orange-brown patch extending from the anal angle to vein Cu1. The homologous patch in females of 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFE6FFD9FBD9FE2DFB4AFDB6" baseAuthorityName="Schaus" baseAuthorityYear="1911" box="[1087,1207,510,536]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colubra">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFE6FFD9FBD9FE2DFB4AFDB6" box="[1087,1207,510,536]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">E. colubra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
only extends to the veinlet between Cu2 and Cu1, and is a distinctly darker orange-brown. Furthermore, the female of 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFE6FFD9FB1EFDF1FA92FD92" baseAuthorityName="Schaus" baseAuthorityYear="1911" box="[1272,1391,546,572]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colubra">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFE6FFD9FB1EFDF1FA92FD92" box="[1272,1391,546,572]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">E. colubra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has subterminal greyish-white shadings between the pm and subterminal lines posterior of vein M3, which are absent in 
<emphasis id="579E2338FFE6FFD9FF55FDB9FD98FD2A" box="[179,613,618,644]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFE6FFD9FF55FDB9FEA0FD2A" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1858" box="[179,349,618,644]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serpentifera">E. serpentifera</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFE6FFD9FE80FDB8FD98FD2A" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1858" box="[358,613,618,644]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serpentifera">Eudocima serpentifera</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
ranges from 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFE6FFD9FD1EFDB8FCC1FD2A" box="[760,828,618,644]" name="Brazil" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Brazil</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFE6FFD9FC94FDB9FC58FD2B" box="[882,933,619,645]" name="Peru" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Peru</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFE6FFD9FC2EFDB8FBE3FD2A" box="[968,1054,618,644]" name="Mexico" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Mexico</collectingCountry>
and the West Indies. A single 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFE6FFD9FA8CFDB8FA61FD2A" box="[1386,1436,618,644]" name="United States of America" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">U.S.</collectingCountry>
record from 
<collectingRegion id="A72E31C8FFE6FFD9FEC5FD5CFE6CFD06" box="[291,401,654,680]" country="United States of America" name="Louisiana" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Louisiana</collectingRegion>
is illustrated in 
<bibRefCitation id="017B82DBFFE6FFD9FDA3FD5DFD2CFD07" author="Brou, V. A." box="[581,721,654,681]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="105 - 108" refId="ref36179" refString="Brou, V. A. (2006) A new US record for the tropical fruit-piercing moth Eudocima serpentifera (Walker, [1858]). Southern Lepidopterists' News, 28, 105 - 108." type="journal article" year="2006">Brou (2006)</bibRefCitation>
. In 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFE6FFD9FD1CFD5CFC89FD06" box="[762,884,654,680]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
it feeds on 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFE6FFD9FC10FD5CFB0AFD06" box="[1014,1271,654,680]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Menispermaceae" genus="Disciphania" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="calocarpa">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFE6FFD9FC10FD5CFB0AFD06" box="[1014,1271,654,680]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Disciphania calocarpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFE6FFD9FAE3FD5CFF37FD63" baseAuthorityName="Zaspel" baseAuthorityYear="2008" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Menispermaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Menispermaceae</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="017B82DBFFE6FFD9FF07FD60FDF0FD62" author="Janzen, D. H. &amp; Hallwachs, W." box="[225,525,690,716]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" refId="ref38340" refString="Janzen, D. H. &amp; Hallwachs, W. (2009) Dynamic database for an inventory of the macrocaterpillar fauna, and its food plants and parasitoides, of Area de Conservacion Guanacaste (ACG), northwestern Costa Rica (nn-SRNP-nnnnn voucher codes). Available from: http: // janzen. sas. upenn. edu (accessed 3 August 2021)" type="url" year="2009">Janzen &amp; Hallwachs 2009</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
